Battery Test: battery neither empty or full, charger plugged in
Battery Test: battery neither empty or full, charger unplugged in
Battery Test: battery full, charger plugged in
When the device is plugged in and its charging state is updated, must set the charging attribute's value to true and fire a chargingchange event.
When the device is plugged in and its charging time is updated, must set the chargingTime attribute's value and fire a chargingtimechange event.
When the device is plugged in and its discharging time is updated, must set the dischargingTime attribute's value to Infinity and fire a dischargingtimechange event.
When the device is plugged in and the battery level is updated, must set the level attribute's value and fire a levelchange event.
When the device is unplugged in and its charging state is updated, must set the charging attribute's value to false and fire a chargingchange event.
When the device is unplugged in and its charging time is updated, must set the chargingTime attribute's value to Infinity and fire a chargingtimechange event.
When the device is unplugged in and its discharging time is updated, must set the dischargingTime attribute's value and fire a dischargingtimechange event.
When the device is plugged in and the battery level is updated, must set the level attribute's value and fire a levelchange event.
